      "rationale": "Mesh sensitivity study performed across three refinement levels (2.1M, 5.4M, 11.8M cells). Grid convergence index computed for wall shear stress and velocity magnitude. GCI for hemolysis-relevant shear stress zones averaged 8.3%, exceeding the 5% threshold at the finest practical mesh due to near-impeller boundary layer constraints. Gradation 2 achieved; Gradation 3 not reached. Claim https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-discretization-orphan supports this finding but lacks traceable derivation from experimental or verification sources."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
